{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel-B variant of the Model Context Protocol tools/call handler: submits the inner request to the running kernel through the offset-region portal and returns the kernel reply as a JSON-RPC result. Renders request_obj to a request string, transmits it through the portal region (the kernel poll loop serves the real tool and writes the reply back into the region), then builds the result two ways per the MCP 2025-06-18 spec: the reply bytes are wrapped as a text content block (the serialized form, required for backwards compatibility, escaped on serialization at this external Channel-A protocol edge), AND, when the reply parses as JSON, the parsed tree is attached as structuredContent so the structure travels through the protocol as structure with no escaping. Writes the JSON-RPC success reply carrying idtext to conn. Requires g_portal_region_base to have been mapped from the inherited portal memfd by the answer-mcp Channel-B entry.","module_name":"serve-protocol-invocation-through-portal-writing-reply","package_name":"serve-protocol-invocation-through-portal-writing-reply","function_definitions":{"serve-protocol-invocation-through-portal-writing-reply":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"conn","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"idtext","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"request_obj","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_type","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"type"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"v_text","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"text"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_content","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","sou